New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo has scored at least 20 points while shooting at least 50% from the floor in each of his 26 games this season, the longest such streak in NBA history.
Key Match Events: The Nets withstood a frantic Milwaukee comeback attempt down the stretch to beat the Bucks 113-110.
The Bucks scored 20 straight points with less than seven minutes left.
Damian Lillard missed two potential tying 3-point attempts in the last 4.1 seconds.
Giannis Antetokounmpo couldn’t finish on his drive to the basket.
Ziaire Williams got the rebound and hit two free throws with 6.1 seconds left.
Post-Match Reflections: The Nets coach Jordi Fernandez said D'Angelo Russell was carried to the locker room in the final minute with what was cramps.
Cam Johnson tweaked his ankle in the final seconds.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Nets went 3-1 against the Bucks this season, including two wins at Milwaukee over the last eight days.
The last time the Nets beat the Bucks as many as three times within the same regular season is 2013-14.
Both teams play at home Saturday, with the Nets facing the Philadelphia 76ers and the Bucks meeting the Portland Trail Blazers.
Others: Andre Jackson Jr. was ejected from the game with 9.9 seconds left in the first half for making unnecessary and excessive contact with Brooklyn’s Nic Claxton.
